    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="367"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">War Trade Board Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Notice Issued by the War Trade Board Section of the Department
                        of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 2, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">W.T.B.R. 829</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">resumption of trade with hungary</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The War Trade Board Section of the Department of State announces that, effective
                    September 2, 1919, the resumption of trade and communication between the United
                    States and Hungary has been authorized, and that, to effect such authorization,
                    the General Enemy Trade License referred to in W.T.B.R. 802, July 14, 1919,<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d367fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_239">p. 239</ref>.</note> has
                    been amended by deleting the words “Hungary or “from paragraph 2 of the
                    limitations upon said General Enemy Trade License.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Exports.</hi>—Exports from the United States to Hungary will
                    be controlled by individual export licenses, but such licenses will be issued
                    freely upon application, except with respect to the following commodities whose
                    exportation to Hungary will be restricted for military reasons:</p>
                <p>[Here follows list identical with that printed in <ref
                        target="frus1919v01#pg_185">volume I, page 185</ref>.]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Imports.</hi>—Imports into the United States from Hungary may
                    take place under General Import License PBF No. 37 (W.T.B.R. 825 issued August
                    15, 1919),<note n="2" xml:id="d367fn2">Not printed.</note> which has been
                    revised and extended, effective September 2, 1919, so as to permit the
                    importation from Hungary, without individual import licenses, of all commodities
                    except those specifically enumerated in paragraphs 1, 2 and 4 of said W.T.B.R.
                    825, paragraph 3 of said Ruling being hereby cancelled and withdrawn.</p>
            </div>
